Class PerformanceEvaluator

java.lang.Object
com.orasaari.PerformanceEvaluator
public class PerformanceEvaluator extends Object
A class to execute performance evaluations. Can be run in the command line or from the UI.

  • Method Details

    • loadScenarios

      private List<PerformanceEvaluator.Scenario> loadScenarios(String filename)
      Load the scenario list from a file. The file format is the Moving AI Lab .scen format. Also, load the maps that are used in the scenarios.
      Parameters:
      filename - filename of the file that is located in MapUtil.SCENARIO_DIRECTORY;
      Returns:
      a list of scenarios including the loaded grid maps

    • getPatfinders

      private Map<Integer,Pathfinder> getPatfinders(List<Integer> algorithms)
      Construct each used pathfinder only once and re-use them in the evaluation.
      Parameters:
      algorithms - a list of algorithms to be used in the evaluation, mapping to constants in MapUtil
      Returns:
      A map of pathfinders: the key is the algorithm code Mapping to MapUtil.ALGORITHM_* and the value is the Pathfinder object.

    • collectEvaluateResults

      private PerformanceEvaluationResults collectEvaluateResults(List<PerformanceEvaluation> evaluationList)
      Collect the evaluation results from Evaluation objects to a PerformanceEvaluationResults.
      Parameters:
      evaluationList - list of all evaluations from a single run
      Returns:
      composed results of evaluations

    • runEvaluation

      PerformanceEvaluationResults runEvaluation(int iterations, String filename, List<Integer> algorithms)

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      The entry point for cases we want to execute from the command line instead of UI. When run from the command line, there is no option to save the results in CSV files.
      Parameters:
      args - No args are used, prepare run options directly to the main method code.
